ible and navigable.Working memories brings together some of current theatre scholarship's fundamental concerns while demonstrating the significance of those concerns to an interdisciplinary readership.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArts in general. 0aDramatic representation. The theater. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Dance / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  adeindustrialization.  aperformativity.  apostindustrial space.  aredevelopment.  astreet theatre.  atheatre historiography.  atheatricality.  aworking memory.1 aCalder, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packagez978311128249740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526147288zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526147288zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526147288/original  a978-3-11-128249-7 Manchester University Press 2019 eBook-Packageb2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA